From 01904838efdaf965fbb6b18163060d03aa2fd733 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcus Figueiredo <figueiredo@protonmail.com>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 04:14:19 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] virtio/gpu: drain deferred read on CtxDetachResource to fix
 pipe UAF

A deferred TransferFromHost3d read runs lock-free on a one-shot "gpu xfer"
thread (see the deferral added earlier). The deferred_guard already makes the
resource-backing lifecycle commands wait_idle on the resource id, but
CtxDetachResource was not covered. On the gfxstream side CtxDetachResource ->
VirtioGpuResource::DetachFromContext sets mHostPipe = nullptr, dropping the last
shared_ptr to the context's RenderThreadPipe and freeing its RenderChannel. If a
deferred read on that resource is mid pipe->TransferFromHost at that moment it
dereferences the freed channel.

Observed as a host SIGSEGV at 0x0 in
VirtioGpuRenderThreadPipe::TransferFromHost, reached via
VirtioGpuResource::TransferRead -> transfer_read_blocking_by_id on the gpu xfer
thread, during SurfaceFlinger/SystemUI composition.

Add CtxDetachResource to the same per-resource wait_idle drain as
attach/detach-backing/unref/create, so the detach (and the pipe free it
triggers) cannot run while a deferred read on that resource is in flight.
---
 src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/worker.rs | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/worker.rs b/src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/worker.rs
index 4a263b4..fbc2f5a 100644
--- a/src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/worker.rs
+++ b/src/devices/src/virtio/gpu/worker.rs
@@ -697,6 +697,17 @@ impl Worker {
                     deferred_guard::wait_idle(info.resource_id)
                 }
                 GpuCommand::ResourceUnref(info) => deferred_guard::wait_idle(info.resource_id),
+                // CtxDetachResource -> VirtioGpuResource::DetachFromContext sets
+                // mHostPipe = nullptr, dropping the last shared_ptr to the context's
+                // RenderThreadPipe and freeing its RenderChannel. A deferred
+                // TransferFromHost3d read on this resource, running lock-free on the
+                // "gpu xfer" thread, is mid pipe->TransferFromHost at that moment and
+                // would dereference the freed channel (observed: SIGSEGV at 0x0 in
+                // VirtioGpuRenderThreadPipe::TransferFromHost). Drain it first, exactly
+                // like the resource-backing commands above.
+                GpuCommand::CtxDetachResource(info) => {
+                    deferred_guard::wait_idle(info.resource_id)
+                }
                 GpuCommand::ResourceCreate2d(info) => deferred_guard::wait_idle(info.resource_id),
                 GpuCommand::ResourceCreate3d(info) => deferred_guard::wait_idle(info.resource_id),
                 GpuCommand::ResourceCreateBlob(info) => {
